//   - Finding.advisory  → result.relatedLocations or rule.help
//   - ReachabilityPath  → result.codeFlows[0].threadFlows[0].locations
//   - Location          → physicalLocation { artifactLocation.uri, region.startLine/startColumn }
//   - Finding with no ReachabilityPath MUST omit codeFlows (an empty codeFlows array
//     invalidates a SARIF document and causes GitHub code scanning to reject the whole upload).
//
// # Analyze Stream Direction and Framing
//
// The Analyze RPC is a server-streaming call: the client (host) sends one AnalyzeRequest
// and the server (plugin) streams zero or more Finding messages back, closing the stream
// when analysis is complete. There is no client-side flow control; the plugin is expected
// to emit findings eagerly as they are discovered. The stream ends normally on a clean
// close; any error terminates the stream and is surfaced to the host as a gRPC status.
// Plugins MUST NOT buffer all findings and send them in a batch; hosts MUST tolerate
// findings arriving in any order.

